body:
In my case the solution was:
Rename your script from tensorflow.py to example.py ... 'import tensorflow'
will import your own script, not tensorflow.

On Thu, Dec 21, 2017 at 6:05 PM, Guenther Schmuelling <
notifications@github.com> wrote:

> The following should work for me on 1.4:
>
> import tensorflow as tf
> from tensorflow import keras
> from keras.layers import Input, Dense
>
> Per 1.4 it was
>
> from tensorflow.contrib import keras
